   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Instead of having the tests only do one type or the other, depending on command line arguments, these tests should be running with both types of wallet. This PR does this by making those tests a subclass of `BitcoinTestFramework` - `BitcoinWalletTestFramework`. This has an overridden `main()` function which calls `BitcoinTestFramework.main()` twice, setting the wallet type before each run. It will still respect the `--descriptor` and `--legacy-wallet` options for those tests.\r\n\r\nThis is built on #20267",
